full_title: the boy is mine by Ariana Grande
title: the boy is mine

description.plain:
“the boy is mine” takes inspiration from the classic ‘90s hit song of the same title by Brandy and Monica. Grande’s track functions as an indirect sequel, according to her in an interview with Zach Sang, it is said to be an elevated version of the leaked/unreleased song “fantasize,” which went viral on TikTok in 2023. Since then, many fans have clamored for a real 90s-inspired pop/R&B record from her.

Prior to the song’s release, in an interview on Apple Music with Zane Lowe, Ariana details how “the boy is mine” and “true story” work as sister tracks, whereas “the boy is mine” is the ‘bad girl anthem’ that “true story” sets up. On the provocative nature of the song and amid accusations of being a homewrecker, she said:

This is a very bad idea, I think, but […] There is a large group of my fans that really do love a bad girl anthem, and this is kind of an elevated version of that.

Following the popular reception of the track and its music video, Brandy and Monica would unite with Grande for the first time, creating a remix of both songs, released on June 21, 2024.
